## The Engines (Core Logic)

[cite_start]These are the active processors that power the ecosystem. [cite: 646]

### SenTient: The Deconstructor
**Status:** *Active Development (Open Source)*
[cite_start]**Technical Classification:** NLP Engine (Entity Reconciliation & Relation Extraction) [cite: 1131, 1138]

[cite_start]To make Orgo and Konnaxion truly independent, I needed a "language deconstructor" that could operate offline, without relying on external LLMs. [cite: 647]
* [cite_start]**The Build:** I merged the best features of **OpenTapioca**, **Falcon**, and **OpenRefine** into a single, streamlined tool. [cite: 648]
* [cite_start]**The Function:** It deconstructs linear human sentences and maps them into structured Wikidata items (concepts). [cite: 649] [cite_start]This process not only secures the entry point but allows information to flow more effectively through internal ducts by removing ambiguity. [cite: 650]
* [cite_start]**The Goal:** Enable language-independent data flow within private bubbles (Orgo) or public networks (Konnaxion). [cite: 651]
* [Access *SenTient* Technical Wiki](SenTient/SenTient-Engine-Hub.md)

### Abstract Wiki Architect
**Status:** *Active Development (Open Source)*
[cite_start]**Technical Classification:** NLG Middleware (Natural Language Generation) [cite: 3, 21]

[cite_start]To make Konnaxion available to all, I needed a way to generate multilingual articles from abstract data. [cite: 652] Since no existing solution was ready, I initiated building this architect.
* [cite_start]**Role:** Structural design and relationship mapping for the wiki ecosystem. [cite: 654]
