### 2. Orgo (The Hermetic Bubble)
[cite_start]**Technical Classification:** Private Enterprise SaaS / ERP Platform [cite: 1073, 1084]

* **Mission:** Organize and Go. [cite_start]A multi-tenant nervous system for organizations (gov, business, schools). [cite: 658]
* [cite_start]**Independence:** Designed to operate in a "bubble" (closed network) for three critical reasons: [cite: 659]
    1.  [cite_start]**Privacy:** Can run completely disconnected from any network, ensuring zero data leakage. [cite: 659]
    2.  [cite_start]**Resilience:** Functions autonomously even if the global internet goes down. [cite: 660]
    3.  [cite_start]**Security:** Minimizes entry points. [cite: 660] [cite_start]All inputs must pass through **SenTient**, which deconstructs the language into safe, structured data before it ever touches the internal system. [cite: 661]
* **[Presentation of Orgo](https://administrative-efficienc-0u6vhrh.gamma.site/)**
* [Access *Orgo* Technical Wiki](Orgo/Orgo-System-Hub.md)

